(16, 'It is a full-bodied, powerful arabica coffee with a hint of acidity which gives a divine balance. Of all the Arabica coffee producing regions, that of the central Tarrazu valley is the most renowned. Also called "Los Santos", the Tarrazu region is a prestigious region of the Central American cordillera, located between 1600 and 2000 m. altitude. In order to preserve its varieties of Arabas such as Typica, Caturra and Villa Sarchi, the state has banned the production of Robusta on its territory. Costa Rican coffee is often used by baristas because of its remarkable quality and body. This coffee is simply tasty!', 1, 2),
